title: 107_s2381
content:
LIQUIDATION OR RELIQUIDATION OF CERTAIN TOMATO SAUCE PREPARATION ENTERED BETWEEN MAY 9, 1992 AND SEPTEMBER 18, 1993. The United States Customs Service shall liquidate or reliquidate entries of tomato sauce preparation within 180 days of receiving a request, regardless of previous classification, at the duty rate for tomato sauce preparation. Requests for reliquidation of entries must be filed within 90 days of the enactment of the Act and contain sufficient information for Customs to locate or reconstruct the entry. Any amounts owed by the US must be paid within 180 days of liquidation or reliquidation. The affected entries are those properly classifiable under subheading 2103.90.60 of the Harmonized Tariff Schedule. Entry numbers and corresponding dates:
